    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>\nOn a straight road of length <b>10<sup>5</sup></b>, <b>n</b> CCTV cameras are placed on different positions <b>p<sub>i</sub></b>. The road starts at <b>p<sub>i</sub></b>=0 and is of length <b>10<sup>5</sup></b>. At <b>time=0</b>, the cameras are switched <b>ON</b> and are facing right. The range of view of each camera <b>r<sub>i</sub></b> is also given i.e if camera is facing right, then <b>p<sub>i</sub></b> to <b>p<sub>i</sub></b>+<b>r<sub>i</sub></b> (both inclusive) and if camera is facing left, then <b>p<sub>i</sub></b>-<b>r<sub>i</sub></b> to <b>p<sub>i</sub></b> (both inclusive) is in the viewing range of that camera. And there is a time period <b>t<sub>i</sub></b> associated with each camera i.e the <b>i</b><sup>th</sup> camera changes its direction from right to left or left to right at all multiples of <b>t<sub>i</sub></b>.</p>\n<p>\nNow, <b>q</b> queries are to be performed. A query contains two integers <b>time</b> and <b>position</b>. The answer to each query is the number of cameras watching that <b>position</b> at that <b>time</b>.\n</p>\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>Input description.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The first line of the input contains an integer <b>T</b> denoting the number of test cases. The description of <b>T</b> test cases follows.</li>\n<li>The first line of each test case contains a single integer <b>n</b> denoting the number of cameras. The second line contains <b>n</b> space-separated distinct integers <b>p<sub>1</sub></b>, <b>p<sub>2</sub></b>, ..., <b>p<sub>n</sub></b> in strictly increasing order denoting the position of each camera on the road.  The third line contains <b>n</b> space-separated integers <b>t<sub>1</sub></b>, <b>t<sub>2</sub></b>, ..., <b>t<sub>n</sub></b> denoting the time period of each camera on the road.  The fourth line contains <b>n</b> space-separated integers <b>r<sub>1</sub></b>, <b>r<sub>2</sub></b>, ..., <b>r<sub>n</sub></b> denoting the range of each camera on the road.\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00a0The next line contains an integer <b>q</b> denoting the number of queries. Each of the next <b>q</b> lines contains 2 integers <b>time</b> and <b>position</b> for which answer is to be calculated.</p>\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>Output description.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>For each test case, the output consists of <b>q</b> lines each containg a single integer <b>count</b> denoting the count of the camera for that query.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>T</b> \u2264 <b>5</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>n</b> \u2264 <b>10000</b></li>\n<li><b>0</b> \u2264 <b>p<sub>i</sub></b> \u2264 <b>100000</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>t<sub>i</sub></b> \u2264 <b>10</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>r<sub>i</sub></b> \u2264 <b>100000</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>q</b> \u2264 <b>100000</b></li>\n<li><b>0</b> \u2264 <b>time</b> \u2264 <b>1000000</b></li>\n<li><b>0</b> \u2264 <b>position</b> \u2264 <b>100000</b></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n2\n3\n0 5 10\n1 3 1\n1 2 1\n5\n0 0\n0 3\n3 3\n4 4\n6 6\n4\n0 2 4 6\n2 1 2 1\n2 2 2 2\n5\n2 0\n0 0\n0 2\n5 5\n6 4\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n1\n0\n1\n1\n1\n1\n1\n2\n2\n2\n</pre><p>\u00a0</p>\n\n<h3>Test Case explanation:</h3>\n<p><b>Case 1</b><br /><br />\nThe direction of each camera changes as shown below-</p>\n<ul>\n<li>For 1st camera at position 0:<br />\nR(0) L(1) R(2) L(3) and so on. </li>\n<li>For 2nd camera at position 5:<br />\nR(0) R(1) R(2) L(3) L(4) L(5) R(6) ...... </li>\n<li>For 3rd camera at position 10:<br />\nR(0) L(1) R(2) L(3) and so on. </li>\n</ul>\n<p>Here, R(i) means the camera is facing right at <b>i</b>th minute.<br /><br />\nAnd L(i) means the camera is facing left at <b>i</b>th minute.</p>\n",
